# This is a Namazu configuration file.
#
#   Originally, this file is named 'namazurc-sample'.  so you should
#   copy this to 'namazurc' to make the file effective.
#
#   Each item is must be separated by one or more SPACE or TAB characters. 
#   You can use a double-quoted string for represanting a string which 
#   contains one or more SPACE or TAB characters like "foo bar baz".
#
#     <List of Directives>
#
#       * Index   : Specify a directory which contains index files (NMZ.*).
#
#       * Replace : Replace a URI string for search results.
#                   Specify TARGET REPLACEMENT.  e.g.,
#
#                     Replace  /www/  http://www.foobar.jp/
#
#                   If you do not want to do the replacement in command
#                   line use, you can run namazu with -U option.
#
#       * Base    : Append <BASE HREF="..."> to a result HTML document.
#                   This value must be terminated with a '/' or '\' character.
#
#       * Logging : Set OFF to turn off keyword logging in NMZ.slog. 
#                   Default: logging ON
#
#	* Lang    : Set a locale code such as `ja_JP.ujis', `ja_JP.sjis', 
#                   `de', etc.  If you set `de' to this, namazu will use 
#                   NMZ.(head|foot|body|msg).de for composing a result 
#                   document and use a proper message catalog for `de'.
#
#	* Scoring : Set a scoring method TFIDF or SIMPLE.
#
#
#   You can use ~/foo notation for representing a pathname of directory 
#   which lacated under your home directory.  e.g., 
#
#      Index  ~/NMZ
#
#Index		/usr/local/var/namazu/index
#Replace	/home/foo/public_html/	http://www.hoge.jp/~foo/
#Base		file://localhost/home/foo/documents/
#Logging	OFF
#Lang		ja_JP.JIS7
#Scoring	TFIDF
